) are expressed in ppm.

Odongrossin H ( 8 ) was obtained as colourless platelets with a molecular formula of C 20 H 30 O 3 , as determined based on the HRESIMS data at m/z 336.2536 [M + NH 4 ] + (calcd 336.2533), which suggested six degrees of unsaturation. The IR spectrum showed absorptions at 3406 and 1770 cm −1 , which were due to one hydroxyl group and one carbonyl group, respectively. The 1 H NMR data ( Table 2 ) demonstrated the presence of two tertiary methyls [ δ H 1.01 (s, H 3 -17) and δ H 0.83 (s, H 3 - 20)]; eight methylenes, including one oxygenated methylene [ δ H 4.45 (d, J = 8.2 Hz, H α -19) and 3.91 (d, J = 8.2 Hz, H β -19)]; four methines, including one oxygenated methine [ δ H 4.34 (m, H-2)]; and a monosubstituted double bond [ δ H 5.82 (dd, J = 17.5, 10.7 Hz, H-15), 4.87 (d, J = 10.7 Hz, Ha-16) and 4.94 (d, J = 17.5 Hz, Hb-16)], which correspond to a dolabrane-type diterpenoid (
). The 13 C NMR data ( Table 3 ) showed one ester carbonyl at δ C
176.9 (C-18). The 1D NMR spectroscopic data of 8 closely resembled those of the previously described notolutesin A ( 9 ) (
), except that an E -double bond at C-3 was reduced in 8 . This was also supported by the HMBC correlation from H 2 -1 and H 2 -3 to C-2 and by the 1 H– 1 H COSY correlation between H-2 and H 2 -3. The NOESY correlation (Fig. S78) of H-2/H 3 -20 suggested that H-2 and H 3 -20 were co-facial and α - oriented. In addition, the NOESY correlations of H 3 -20/H-12 α , H-12 β / H 3 -17, H-12 β /H-10, H-10/H-19 β , H-19 β /H-4 and H-19 β /H-8 implied that they were β -oriented. Accordingly, the relative configuration of 8 was determined. The absolute configuration was confirmed by ECD calculations, as presented in Fig. S83E. Consequently, 8 was established as 2 S , 4 R , 5 R , 8 S , 9 S , 10 R , 13 S .

