Quantitative real-time PCR was used to investigate the expression of hyphal-related genes under the treatment of 1 (
).
C. albicans DSY
654 (5 × 10 6 cells/mL in the RPMI 1640 medium) was challenged with 1 at a suitable concentration of 32 μ g/mL at 37 ° C for 6 h with shaking at 200 rpm. At the end of the incubation period, cells were collected and washed twice with PBS . The total RNA was isolated via a hot phenol method (
), and cDNA was synthesized using a cDNA synthesis kit (TaKaRa Biotechnology, Dalian, China ). PCR was conducted with the SYBR Green master mix (TaKaRa Biotechnology, Dalian, China ) in an Eppendorf Mastercycler Real-Time PCR System. The primer sequences used for gene amplification are listed in Table S2. A housekeeping gene, namely, 18 S rRNA, was used as an internal control.
